O’Reilly’s Summer Internship Program is an in-person, 10-week, paid, summer program that offers students the opportunity to work closely with experienced leaders and professionals in different departments and to showcase their knowledge by providing recommendations and feedback. Throughout the internship, students will build upon their current skillsets, while applying their education to meaningful, impactful projects.Interns will be paired with one department for the summer and will be responsible for assisting their team with special projects and daily tasks that will contribute to the success of the company. Along with a mentor, interns will design their Career Development Plan and complete tasks and projects to gain the experience necessary to achieve their career goals.What You Will Gain:Opportunities to analyze and improve internal cross reference/product match databaseOpportunities to assist in developing Business Intelligence resources from MOTOR professional customer dataOwnership over a meaningful project and/or tasks that will challenge you to leave a lasting impact on O’ReillyA personalized Career Development Plan with the guidance of your mentorIntern Cohort: complete the program as part of a tight-knit group of interns supporting & learning from each otherGain exclusive industry knowledge with site visits to our stores and distribution centersProfessional development curriculum with events hosted by experienced professionalsBuild connections with O’Reilly team members and fellow interns through social events and activitiesExpert education on translating your internship experience to your future job searchBelow is a list of things we’d like to see in candidates for this internship. However, above all else, we are looking for the right PERSON for the job. Our ideal intern is hardworking, enthusiastic to learn and use new skills, dedicated to always doing their best, excited to contribute to a culture of teamwork, and committed to approaching their work with a win-win attitude to help everyone succeed.We’d Love to Hear From Students Who:See themselves in O’Reilly’s 12 Culture ValuesHave knowledge of Excel, SQL, and a computer language such as Python, C, C#, and/or JavaAre actively enrolled at an accredited college or university pursuing a Bachelor’s degree in a related fieldAre entering their junior or senior year of college (minimum 60 completed credit hours), or be a graduate studentParticipate in on or off-campus activities outside of the classroomExcellent communicators, both verbal and writtenPassionate about contributing to and being a part of a positive culture based on win-win attitudesContribute to their local community through community outreach, service projects, etc.Ability to work full-time (40 hours) for 10 weeks during summerO’Reilly Auto Parts has a proven track record of growth and stability. O’Reilly is full of successful career stories and believes in a strong promote-from-within philosophy, encouraging you to grow your career along with the organization. Total Compensation Package:Competitive Wages & Paid Time OffStock Purchase Plan & 401k with Employer Contributions Starting Day OneMedical, Dental, & Vision Insurance with Optional Flexible Spending Account (FSA)Team Member Health/Wellbeing ProgramsTuition Educational Assistance ProgramsOpportunities for Career GrowthO’Reilly Auto Parts is an equal opportunity employer. The Company does not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin or ancestry (including immigration status or citizenship), sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, pregnancy (including childbirth, lactation, and related medical conditions,) age (40 and over), veteran status, uniformed service member status, physical or mental disability, genetic information (including testing or characteristics) or another protected status as defined by local, state, or federal law, as applicable.Qualified individuals with a disability may be entitled to reasonable accommodation under the Americans with Disabilities Act. technical solutions - With support from and close collaboration with organizational partners, an aspiration for this internship is to help set the groundwork for deployment and “productionization” of model pipelines.   Exposure to real-world data and observational research/real-world evidence as well as the US health care system and the pharmaceutical/biotechnology industry. Knowledge sharing with and presentations to key stakeholders, including technical and non-technical audiences. Co-author communications for dissemination at research conference(s) or peer-reviewed scientific journals.Program HighlightsIntensive 12-weeks, full-time (40 hours per week) paid internship.Program start dates are in June (Summer)A stipend, based on location, will be provided to help alleviate (Required) Required Education: You meet one of the following criteria:Must be pursuing a Master's Degree (enrolled student).Must have attained a Master's Degree.Must be pursuing a PhD (enrolled student).Must have attained a PhD.Required Majors: Computer Science, Data Science, Biostatistics, Bioinformatics, Epidemiology, Health Economics, or related quantitative disciplines.Required Skills: In-depth knowledge of advanced Machine Learning techniques (e.g., ensemble learning, neural networks) as applied to both structured and unstructured data.Strong programming skills in SQL and processing.Preferred Knowledge, Skills, and QualificationsExcellent communication, collaboration, and interpersonal skills.Complements our culture and the standards that guide our daily behavior &
